message.content:
cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with coded caching delivery and proposes a state-adaptive scheme to improve the rate and decoding latency. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper considers a symmetric noisy broadcast channel and models the delivery phase by a state-dependent broadcast channel. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the proposed scheme involves adapting to the state of the channel, which can be seen as a control problem. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may be relevant as the paper proposes a new scheme for coded caching, which involves designing algorithms for cache placement and delivery. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) may be relevant as the paper deals with delivery of multimedia content over a broadcast channel.
